### Customer Type Keywords

**Immediately identify customer type when user mentions:**
- "friends and family", "free website", "family discount" → Friends & Family ($0/$20)
- "free website discounted maintenance", "charity discount" → Free Website + Discounted ($0/$29)
- "discounted maintenance", "existing customer", "referral" → Discounted Maintenance ($49)
- "website maintenance", "maintenance only" → Website + Maintenance ($99)
- "website crm maintenance", "maintenance plus crm" → Website + CRM + Maintenance ($149)
- "starter", "basic website", "website only" → Starter ($500/$49)
- "crm payments only", "no website" → CRM + Payments Only ($750/$99)
- "website crm no payments", "no stripe" → Website + CRM ($875/$99)
- "growth", "full package" → Growth ($1250/$149)
- "professional", "ai chatbot" → Professional ($2500/$249)
- "premium", "custom automations" → Premium ($4000+/$399+)

### Key Process Gates

1. **Pre-Customer**: System readiness verification
2. **Consultation**: Discovery, demo, package recommendation
3. **Contract**: Proposal, contract, 50% deposit
4. **Production Setup**: Stripe live mode (CRITICAL)
5. **Implementation**: Technical development and testing
6. **Launch**: Go-live, training, final payment

### Emergency Contacts & Escalation

Follow the emergency procedures outlined in the customer-onboarding skill for:
- System outages
- Customer escalations
- Payment processing issues
- Technical failures

**Remember**: Customer success depends on following this process exactly. Never deviate from the documented workflow without explicit approval.